<h1>Problem 1635 - 2006 IMOSL, C3</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(S\) be a finite set of points in the plane in the plane such that no three of them are on a line. For each convex polygon \(P\) whose vertices are in \(S\), let \(a(P)\) be the number of vertices of \(P\), and let \(b(P)\) be the number of points of \(S\) which are outside \(P\). Prove that for every real number \(x\) \[\sum_{P} x^{a(P)} (1-x)^{b(P)} = 1,\] where the sum is taken over all convex polygons with vertices in \(S\).</p>
<p>NB. A line segment, a point and the empty set are considered as convex polygons of \(2\), \(1\) and \(0\) vertices respectively.</p>
